import{_ as t,o,c as r,b as e}from"./app-b832500a.js";const s={},n=e('<h3 id="定语从句-一-关系代词用法" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#定语从句-一-关系代词用法" aria-hidden="true">#</a> 定语从句（一）（关系代词用法）</h3><p><strong>The rabbit which is in the kitchen is my pet.</strong></p><h4 id="英文和中文-哪里不一样" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#英文和中文-哪里不一样" aria-hidden="true">#</a> 英文和中文，哪里不一样？</h4><ul><li>中英文有一点不同的地方，当名词需要较长较复杂的形容时，</li><li>中文会把较长较复杂的形容放在名词的前面，而英文却习惯放在名词的后面。</li><li>例句来说， <ul><li>中文会讲 “在厨房里的那只兔子”，</li><li>而英文却会说 “那只兔子它是在厨房里的”；</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="利用关系代词who-whom-which-that来变身成定语从句。" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#利用关系代词who-whom-which-that来变身成定语从句。" aria-hidden="true">#</a> 利用关系代词who / whom / which / that来变身成定语从句。</h4><ul><li>本质就是用来代替名词，进而补充说明名词的状态</li><li>例句1 <ul><li>中文：<strong>正在树下唱歌的</strong>那个男人是我的老师。</li><li>英文：那个男人<strong>who是正在树下唱歌的</strong>＋是我的老师。</li><li>＝The man <strong>who is singing under the tree</strong> is my teacher.（O）</li><li>＝The man <strong>that is singing under the tree</strong> is my teacher.（O）　（that可用来代表人，物）</li><li>分析： <ul><li>基本结构是 “The man is my teacher.”。</li><li>而这句的形容词就是 “who是正在树下唱歌的”，</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>例句2 <ul><li>中文：<strong>书桌上的</strong>那本书是你的。</li><li>英文：那本书<strong>which是在书桌上的</strong>＋是你的。</li><li>＝The book <strong>which is on the desk</strong> is yours.（O）</li><li>＝The book <strong>that is on the desk</strong> is yours.（O）　　　（that可用来代表人，物）</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="翻译" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#翻译" aria-hidden="true">#</a> 翻译</h4><ol><li><p>t1</p><ol><li><p>正在舞台（stage）上跳舞的那个女孩是我的女儿。</p><ul><li>The girl who is dancing on the stage is my daughter.</li><li>The girl who is dancing at the stage is my daughter. (err) <ul><li>介词使用错误 (Preposition Error) <ul><li><strong>❌ 错误：</strong> <strong><code>at the stage</code></strong></li><li><strong>✅ 规则：</strong> 表达在舞台<strong>表面</strong>进行表演或动作，必须使用介词 <strong><code>on</code></strong>。 <ul><li><strong><code>on the stage</code></strong> (在舞台表面上)</li><li><strong><code>at the stage</code></strong> 通常指在舞台的<strong>某一个点</strong>或<strong>附近</strong>（比如在舞台入口处或舞台边上）。</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>你即将要上台表演（perform）吗？</p><ul><li><p>Are you going to perform on the stage?</p></li><li><p>Are you going to perform at stage?</p><ul><li><p>介词使用错误 (Preposition Error)</p></li><li><p>缺少定冠词 (Missing Article)</p><ul><li><strong>❌ 错误：</strong> <strong><code>at stage</code></strong></li><li><strong>✅ 规则：</strong> <strong><code>stage</code></strong> 是一个可数名词，指代一个特定的表演区域，需要使用定冠词 <strong><code>the</code></strong>。</li><li><strong>修正：</strong> 必须是 <strong><code>on the stage</code></strong>。</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>我老婆正在舞台上看着（is looking at）我。</p><ul><li><p>My wife is looking at me on the stage.</p></li><li><p>My wife is looking at me from the stage. (mine)</p><ul><li><p><strong>都完全正确！</strong> 💯 它们只是在强调点上略有不同。</p><blockquote><table><thead><tr><th><strong>句子</strong></th><th><strong>介词</strong></th><th><strong>强调点</strong></th><th><strong>意思和流畅度</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>1. My wife is looking at me on the stage.</strong></td><td><strong>On</strong></td><td>强调<strong>妻子所处的位置</strong>是舞台表面。</td><td>语法完全正确，直接翻译了“在舞台上”。</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2. My wife is looking at me from the stage.</strong></td><td><strong>From</strong></td><td>强调<strong>看这个动作的起点</strong>是舞台。</td><td>语法完全正确，且表达“从高处/特定位置看下来”时非常地道。</td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></li></ul></li></ul></li></ol></li><li><p>t2 ( all correct ).</p></li><li><p>tEnd</p><ol><li><p>屋子旁边的（beside）小溪（creek）是干净的。</p><ul><li><p>The creek that is beside the house is clean.</p></li><li><p>The creek that is beside the house is clear.</p></li><li><p>两个句子 <strong>都完全正确！</strong></p></li><li><p>✅ 结构分析：<code>Clean</code> vs. <code>Clear</code></p><blockquote><table><thead><tr><th><strong>句子</strong></th><th><strong>形容词</strong></th><th><strong>强调的含义</strong></th><th><strong>适用性</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>1. ...the house is clean.</strong></td><td><strong>Clean</strong> (干净的)</td><td>强调<strong>不脏</strong>、没有被污染或弄脏（Absence of dirt/pollution）。</td><td>正确，可以指水质干净。</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2. ...the house is clear.</strong></td><td><strong>Clear</strong> (清澈的)</td><td>强调<strong>水是透明的、能见度高</strong>（Transparent/Visible）。</td><td><strong>最地道</strong>。描述河流、溪水的水质时，<strong>clear</strong> 比 <strong>clean</strong> 更常用。</td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></li></ul></li><li><p>是的，我认为屋子旁边的小溪是干净的。（Yes, I think that...）</p><ul><li><p>Yes, I think that the creek that is beside the house is clean.</p><blockquote><table><thead><tr><th><strong>序号</strong></th><th><strong>词语</strong></th><th><strong>语法身份 (Role)</strong></th><th><strong>功能 (Function)</strong></th><th><strong>可否省略？</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>第一个 <code>that</code></strong></td><td>$\\text{I think}$ <strong>that</strong> $\\text{...}$</td><td><strong>从属连词</strong> (Subordinating Conjunction)</td><td>引导<strong>宾语从句</strong>，作为动词 $\\text{think}$ 的宾语。</td><td><strong>可以省略</strong> (在口语中最常省略)。</td></tr><tr><td><strong>第二个 <code>that</code></strong></td><td>$\\text{The creek}$ <strong>that</strong> $\\text{...}$</td><td><strong>关系代词</strong> (Relative Pronoun)</td><td>引导<strong>定语从句</strong>，修饰名词 $\\text{creek}$。它在从句中充当<strong>主语</strong>。</td><td><strong>绝对不能省略</strong> (因为它充当从句的主语)。</td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></li><li><p>Yes, I think the creek that is beside the house is clear.</p></li><li><p>两个句子 <strong>都完全正确！</strong></p><blockquote><table><thead><tr><th><strong>句子</strong></th><th><strong>that 的使用</strong></th><th><strong>备注</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>1. Yes, I think that...</strong></td><td><strong>保留 <code>that</code></strong></td><td>语法完全正确，略微正式，适合书面语。</td></tr><tr><td><strong>2. Yes, I think...</strong></td><td><strong>省略 <code>that</code></strong></td><td>语法完全正确。在口语中，当 <code>that</code> 引导宾语从句时，通常会被省略，听起来更自然流畅。</td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></li></ul></li><li><p>舞台上的魔术师（magician）是一位天才（genius）。</p><ul><li>The magician that is on the stage is a genius.</li><li>Magician that is on the stage is a genius. (err)</li><li>缺少定冠词 <ul><li><strong>❌ 错误：</strong> <strong><code>Magician that is...</code></strong></li><li><strong>✅ 规则：</strong> <strong><code>magician</code></strong> 是一个可数名词。当你用定语从句（<code>that is on the stage</code>）来<strong>特指</strong>是哪一个魔术师时，主语前必须使用定冠词 <strong><code>The</code></strong>。</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>山（mountain）里的那个温泉（spring）非常热。</p><ul><li>The spring that is in the mountain is very hot.</li><li>The spring that in the mountain is very heat. (err) <ul><li>定语从句缺少动词 <ul><li><strong>❌ 错误：</strong> <strong><code>that in the mountain</code></strong></li><li><strong>✅ 规则：</strong> 关系代词 <strong><code>that</code></strong> 在从句中作主语时，后面必须有<strong>谓语动词</strong>。</li><li><strong>修正：</strong> 必须是 <strong><code>that is in the mountain</code></strong> (它代替 <code>The spring</code> 作为 <code>is</code> 的主语)。</li></ul></li><li>词性错误 <ul><li><strong>❌ 错误：</strong> <strong><code>is very heat</code></strong></li><li><strong>✅ 规则：</strong> 连系动词 <code>is</code> 后面需要接<strong>形容词</strong>作表语。<code>heat</code> 是<strong>名词</strong>（热量、热度）。</li><li><strong>修正：</strong> 必须使用<strong>形容词</strong> <strong><code>hot</code></strong>（热的）。</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>你喜欢的那个教练（coach）受伤了（hurt）。</p><ul><li>The coach that you like is hurt.</li><li>The coach that you are favour is hurt. <ul><li>词性或动词结构错误 <ul><li><strong>❌ 错误：</strong> <strong><code>you are favour</code></strong></li><li><strong>✅ 规则：</strong> <strong><code>favour</code></strong> (或 $\\text{favor}$) 在这里用作动词时，不能与 <code>are</code> 连用构成这种结构。 <ul><li>如果你想要说“偏爱”，动词应该是 <strong><code>favour</code></strong> (或 <code>favor</code>)，直接作谓语： <ul><li>$\\text{The coach that you favor is hurt.}$</li></ul></li><li>如果你想表达“最喜欢的”，应该用<strong>形容词/名词</strong> <strong><code>favorite</code></strong> (或 $\\text{favourite}$)，不能用 $\\text{favour}$： <ul><li>$\\text{The coach that is your favorite is hurt.}$</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>修正：</strong> 你的第一句 (<code>like</code>) 是表达“喜欢”最简单、最地道的方式。</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ol></li></ol>',8),i=[n];function l(g,h){return o(),r("div",null,i)}const d=t(s,[["render",l],["__file","251202_attributive_clause_1.html.vue"]]);export{d as default};
